ng through Upper Guk and Lower Guk, it is extremely<br>important to know that you cannot kill anything or help anyone!  This<br>also holds true while in the swamp.  The main inhabitants of Guk are<br>Frogloks and as a paladin, we do not start off Killed on Sight (KOS) to<br>them.  However, if you attack one and kill it or help someone kill one<br>(and this includes taunting, healing, rooting etc.), you will take a<br>faction hit and become KOS to the frogs.  With that being said, the trip<br>is very easy and you can wander all over Upper Guk and explore at<br>leisure.<br><br>Once in Lower Guk you will want to stay near the zone line.  In Lower<br>Guk there is an added danger, undead frogs.  These undead frogs will<br>attempt to kill you so do not go near them.  The armor drops very near<br>the zone border off of the following: Shin Gauntlets drop off of Shin<br>Knights and Shin Greaves drop off of Shin Ghoul Knights.  It helps to<br>let people at the zone border know your intentions and, hopefully, they<br>will help you get the armor.  People usually let the armor rot as it is<br>useless to people hunting the zone for experience and loot.<br><br>There is one last warning that deserves it's own paragraph.  If you hear<br>someone shout &quot;Train,&quot; don't think twice about it but just zone to Upper<br>Guk!  The monsters here are very powerful and would like nothing more<br>than to eat you so just zone out at the first sign of trouble.<br><br>All in all these pieces are very easy to get and will last you through<br>many levels if you get them early.  Good luck!<br> <p>Islington Angelwatch <br>Paladin of 40 seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr<br>Proud Member of Hearts of Valor</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kleitus>Kleitus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.mcs.kent.edu/~rheath/Kleitus_pics/kleitus-small.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 11/17/00 10:21:4